  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale dataset)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A model revision was issued on 2025-11-14 to update the impeller tip-clearance geometry and re-tune the turbulence damping coefficient; the primary experimental hemolysis dataset (dataVintage 2025-10-22) predates this revision by approximately three weeks. The assessment narrative argues the geometry change was not material to the dataset's relevance because the impeller swept volume changed by less than 0.4 %, and no formal re-validation was performed against the revised model build. Decision: Accepted.",
